6.  The tasks of the team leader include:  

(i)  act as ADB's main point of contact for bank financial analysis experts, maintain 
regular contact with ADB, and coordinate and disseminate information in both 
directions;  
(ii)  set work schedules and ensure deadlines are met;  
(iii)  review  draft  and  final  draft  banking  system  analyses  produced  by  the  bank 
financial analysis experts;  
(iv)  review draft and final draft credit applications produced by the bank financial 
analysis experts;  
(v)  provide quality control and ensure coherence of the work of the bank financial 
analysis experts;  
(vi)  coordinate  with  ADB  and  appropriate  government  and  finance  sector  DMC 
entities to arrange dates and other logistics for due diligence;  
(vii)  conduct missions and seminars to disseminate findings from the DMC banks and 
central bank officials; and,  
(viii)  organize seminars with the trade finance expert and ADB staff.  

7.  Qualifications of the team leader include: 

(i)  master’s degree, or equivalent, in business administration, finance, economics, 
or a related field; 
(ii)  at least 10 years of relevant work experience; 
(iii)  strong knowledge of financial institutions, risk assessments, and country risk 
analysis; 
(iv)  experience working in and/or with financial institutions; 
(v)  significant international experience working in emerging markets; 
(vi)  significant experience in financial analysis and due diligence on banks;  
(vii)  excellent oral and written communication skills in English; and 
(viii)  willingness to travel extensively.  

2.  Bank Financial Analysis Experts (9 international consultants; total of 108 
person-months) 

8.  Scope  of  work.  The  experts  will  work  in  the  field  with  ADB  TFP  relationship 
managers to analyze DMC banks located throughout Asia and the Pacific. The work will 
require extensive travel. 

9.  The core of experts’ work will be: (i) financial analysis, (ii) due diligence, and, (iii) 
writing of credit applications and reports. 

10.  The tasks of the experts include:  

(i)  acquire  financial  and  credit  information,  including  reports  from  credit  rating 
agencies, on targeted DMC banks;  
(ii)  perform risk ratings on each bank using ADB's risk-rating model;  
(iii)  conduct financial, ratio, gap, and other analyses of financial information;  
(iv)  conduct due diligence on the DMC banks by (a) meeting with the banks; (b) 
assessing  corporate  governance,  anti-money  laundering  policies  and 
management capabilities; and, (c) asking questions that arise from the financial 
analyses;

