C.  Deliverables and Reporting Requirements for the Consulting Firm 

15.  The consulting firm will: 

(i)  provide regular reports and updates on work progress by the bank financial 
analysis experts; 
(ii)  submit  approximately  80  high-quality  and  cohesive  annual  reviews, 
approximately 10 new credit applications, and 24 banking system analyses; 
(iii)  conduct two knowledge-sharing seminars with importers and exporters, DMC 
bank staff, and government officials; and 
(iv)  conduct in-house seminars in two DMC banks.
